12 SECTION 1.1.(a) G.S. 135-4(g) reads as rewritten:
13 "(g) Teachers All of the following apply to teachers and other State employees who served
14 in the uniformed services services, as defined in the Uniformed Services Employment and
15 Reemployment Rights Act of 1994, 38 U.S.C. § 4303, who (i) were not dishonorably discharged,
16 and who discharged and (ii) returned to the service of the State within a period of two years from
17 date of discharge shall discharge:
18 (1) The member shall be credited with prior service for such the period of service
19 in the uniformed services for the maximum period that they are the member
20 is entitled to reemployment under the Uniformed Services Employment and
21 Reemployment Rights Act of 1994, 38 U.S.C. § 4301, et seq., or other federal
22 law, and the law.
23 (2) The salary or compensation of such a the teacher or State employee during
24 that period of service credited under subdivision (1) of this subsection is
25 deemed to be that salary or compensation the employee would have received
26 but for the period of service had the employee remained continuously
27 employed, if the determination of that salary or compensation is reasonably
28 certain. If the determination of the salary or compensation is not reasonably
29 certain, then it is deemed to be that employee's average rate of compensation
30 during the 12-month period immediately preceding the period of service.
31 (3) When a member who has served in the uniformed services returns to work in
32 compliance with the conditions of this subsection, that member's employer
33 shall remit to the System all employer and employee contributions for the full
34 period of that member's military service.
