23 LEGISLATIVE RETIREMENT SYSTEM REEMPLOYMENT FLEXIBILITY
24 SECTION 1.4.(a) G.S. 135-3(a)(8)c. reads as rewritten:
25 "c. Unless otherwise provided, if a beneficiary who retired on an early or
26 service retirement allowance under this Article is reemployed by, or
27 otherwise engaged to perform services for, an employer participating
28 in the Retirement System on a part time, temporary, interim, or on a
29 fee for service basis, whether contractual or otherwise, and if the
30 beneficiary earns an amount during the 12 month period immediately
31 following the effective date of retirement or in any calendar year which
32 exceeds fifty percent (50%) of the reported compensation, excluding
33 terminal payments, during the 12 months of service preceding the
34 effective date of retirement, or twenty thousand dollars ($20,000),
35 whichever is greater, as hereinafter indexed, then the retirement
36 allowance shall be suspended as of the first day of the month following
37 the month in which the reemployment earnings exceed the indexed
38 amount, for the balance of the calendar year, unless the reemployment
39 earnings exceed the indexed amount in the month of December. If the
40 reemployment earnings exceed the indexed amount in December, then
41 the retirement allowance shall not be suspended. A suspended
42 retirement allowance of the beneficiary shall be reinstated as of
43 January 1 of each year following suspension. The amount that may be
44 earned before suspension shall be increased on January 1 of each year
45 by the percentage change between the December Consumer Price
46 Index in the year prior to retirement and the December Consumer Price
47 Index in the year most recently ended, calculated to the nearest tenth
48 of a percent (1/10 of 1%), provided that this percentage change is
49 positive. This sub-subdivision shall not apply to service as a member
50 of the Legislative Retirement System of North Carolina under Article
51 1A of Chapter 120 of the General Statutes."
