31 SECTION 1.5. Article 86 of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes is amended by
32 adding a new section to read:
33 "§ 58-86-41. Collection and reporting of contributions.
34 (a) Under rules adopted by the Board, each eligible fire department and each eligible
35 rescue or emergency medical services squad shall, on account of each eligible firefighter and
36 each eligible rescue squad worker, certify any information necessary for the proper
37 administration of the Pension Fund. The submission of this information by an eligible fire
38 department or an eligible rescue or emergency medical services squad constitutes a certification
39 of its accuracy.
40 (b) Each eligible fire department and each eligible rescue or emergency medical services
41 squad shall transmit contributions as certified under subsection (a) of this section on the forms
42 prescribed by the Board."
