43 LEIA MODIFICATIONS
44 SECTION 1.11.(a) G.S. 135-7(h) reads as rewritten:
45 "(h) Legislative Enactment Implementation Arrangement. – The Legislative Enactment
46 Implementation Arrangement, or LEIA, is established effective October 1, 2017, and placed
47 under the management of the Board of Trustees. The purpose of the LEIA is to provide for timely
48 and ongoing administrative implementation of legislative provisions regarding the retirement of,
49 or payment of retirement benefits to, public officers or public employees. The LEIA shall have
50 the following parameters:
Page 10 House Bill 1126-Third Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) Administration. – The LEIA shall be administered by the Board of Trustees,
2 which shall compile and maintain all records necessary or appropriate for
3 administration. The Board of Trustees shall have full discretionary authority
4 to interpret, construe, and implement the LEIA and to adopt such rules and
5 regulations as may be necessary or desirable to implement the provisions of
6 the LEIA.
7 (2) Funding of the LEIA. – In the event that (i) the General Assembly creates or
8 modifies any provision for the retirement of, or payment of retirement benefits
9 to, public officers or public employees that has a cost savings as measured by
10 actuarial note required by Article 15 of Chapter 120 of the General Statutes,
11 or (ii) the Board of Trustees identifies a specific administrative or information
12 technology purpose that is necessary to prevent an interruption to the normal
13 operation of the Retirement System, the Board of Trustees may direct up to
14 one hundredth percent (0.01%) of the required contributions to fund the LEIA.
15 These funds must be deposited in a separate fund from the fund into which
16 regular employer contributions are deposited for the Retirement System. The
17 Board of Trustees shall not direct any employer contributions into the LEIA
18 after January 1, 2035.
19 (3) Allocation of LEIA funds. – The Board of Trustees may allocate LEIA funds
20 to (i) the implementation of legislative provisions regarding the retirement of,
21 or payment for retirement benefits to, public officers or public employees, or
22 (ii) be used for administrative or information technology purposes, subject to
23 the following restrictions:
24 a. The Board of Trustees must identify individual implementation
25 projects that will be paid for with LEIA funds. These implementation
26 projects must be necessitated by a specific statute or session law that
27 was enacted within five years of the allocation of the funds. The Board
28 of Trustees must also identify the number of years for which each
29 individual implementation project will be paid for with LEIA funds.
30 b. For implementation projects that will be paid for with LEIA funds for
31 a period of one year or less, the Board of Trustees must determine that
32 the cost savings from implementing the project is projected to be no
33 less than half of the amount of LEIA funds utilized to pay for
34 implementation.
35 c. For implementation projects that will be paid for with LEIA funds for
36 a period of greater than one year, but not more than four years, the
37 Board of Trustees must determine that the long-term cost savings from
38 implementing the project is projected to be at least three times greater
39 than the cost of implementation.
40 d. No implementation project shall be paid for with LEIA funds for a
41 period of more than four years.
42 e. The Board of Trustees shall identify the specific administrative or
43 information technology purpose for which LEIA funds will be used.
44 Any use of LEIA funds for administrative or information technology
45 purposes requires a determination by the Board of Trustees that the
46 use of funds is necessary to prevent an interruption to the normal
47 operation of the Retirement System.purposes that the Board of
48 Trustees determines are necessary to prevent an interruption to the
49 normal operation of the Retirement System.
50 (4) Treatment of unused assets. – Any assets of the LEIA not used to pay allowed
51 administrative expenses for timely administrative implementation of
