21 ALLOW MATERNITY BENEFITS FOR ALL ELIGIBLE DEPENDENT
22 CHILDREN/REMOVE REFERENCE TO MATERNITY BENEFITS FROM THE
23 STATUTE DEALING WITH CATEGORIES OF COVERAGE
24 SECTION 2.1.(a) G.S. 135-48.43(d) reads as rewritten:
25 "(d) Categories of Coverage Available. – There The following are four categories of
26 coverage which that an employee or retiree may elect.elect:
27 (1) Employee Only. – Covers enrolled employees only. Maternity benefits are
28 provided to employee only.
29 (2) Employee and Child. – Covers enrolled employee and all eligible dependent
30 children. Maternity benefits are provided to the employee only.
31 (3) Employee and Family. – Covers employee and spouse, and all eligible
32 dependent children. Maternity benefits are provided to employee or enrolled
33 spouse.
34 (4) Employee and Spouse. – Covers employee and spouse only. Maternity
35 benefits are provided to the employee or the employee's enrolled spouse."
